1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:04,524
A visual canvas becomes more valuable as the analysis grows,

2
00:00:04,524 --> 00:00:08,967
but only if you can still find the relevant evidence.

3
00:00:08,967 --> 00:00:13,411
QualCanvas includes layout and navigation controls that help without changing

4
00:00:13,411 --> 00:00:14,744
your coding decisions.

5
00:00:15,144 --> 00:00:19,441
Choose Fit View when nodes have moved beyond the visible area.

6
00:00:19,441 --> 00:00:23,348
Start from the full structure, then zoom or pan toward

7
00:00:23,348 --> 00:00:27,255
the source, code or memo you need instead of repeatedly

8
00:00:27,255 --> 00:00:29,208
dragging the canvas at random.

9
00:00:29,608 --> 00:00:34,006
Open More canvas actions and choose Auto-arrange layout when the

10
00:00:34,006 --> 00:00:36,644
workspace needs a clean starting point.

11
00:00:36,644 --> 00:00:41,042
Auto-arrange changes positions; it does not decide what your evidence

12
00:00:41,042 --> 00:00:44,560
means or rewrite the analytical links you created.

13
00:00:44,960 --> 00:00:48,732
Press Control K to open the command palette.

14
00:00:48,732 --> 00:00:54,390
Search for a canvas action, run it and return to the analysis.

15
00:00:54,390 --> 00:00:59,576
Keyboard shortcuts are especially useful during repeated coding and review sessions.

16
00:00:59,976 --> 00:01:03,952
Open Sources when you need a stable route back to

17
00:01:03,952 --> 00:01:05,542
an interview or response.

18
00:01:05,542 --> 00:01:09,518
The visual layout should support the evidence trail, not replace

19
00:01:09,518 --> 00:01:11,904
careful reading of the source material.

20
00:01:12,304 --> 00:01:16,361
Switch between light and dark display modes for the working

21
00:01:16,361 --> 00:01:17,984
environment that suits you.

22
00:01:17,984 --> 00:01:22,042
On a phone, use the canvas for quick review; detailed

23
00:01:22,042 --> 00:01:25,288
visual organisation is clearer on a larger screen.

24
00:01:25,688 --> 00:01:29,888
Fit the view, arrange when useful, search for commands and

25
00:01:29,888 --> 00:01:31,988
keep returning to the source.

26
00:01:31,988 --> 00:01:36,188
Continue in the training centre with the repository tutorial for

27
00:01:36,188 --> 00:01:39,128
organising insights across more than one project.
